<h1>Katrina Grigg-Saito</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://katrinagriggsaito.com/now/">katrinagriggsaito.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
San Francisco
CA
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Writer, Fishbird, Artist, Unicorn. I work with artists and writers and students and my amazing editors at Little, Brown and Company.
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I fall in love with alarming regularity.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I write because I love it. I write because I want to jump into the hearts of people and splash around. I write because I have a lot of questions and because I fall in love with strange things like How To Mourn.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
Oof. Profound. Um, right now I love this tea ceremony haiku for its stark insistence that we continue on. Keeping from getting upset. Keeping on making tea. It is the end of the year.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
A Tale For The Time Being, Ruth Ozeki <<a href="http://theabsurdityofwriting.tumblr.com/post/123430976341/love-letter-ruth-ozeki>">http://theabsurdityofwriting.tumblr.com/post/123430976341/love-letter-ruth-ozeki></a>
</p>

